commit.message:
common: Fix VAD calculations

- For ordinary VAD we iterated backwards, which is wrong.
- For retroactive VAD we muted blocks which we should not.
readme: Add note about MinGW build failure

fst: Use fixed size types to for fst typedefs

This fixes wrong t_fstPtrInt size in x64 plugin compiled with VS2022.

closes #129

fst: Handle EditIdle

When running vst2 JUCE gui in Carla on Linux - the window is always
black and never updated. When GUI is opened JUCE expects that hosts
would drive event loop with effEditIdle messages.

The only event that plugin continuously receives has opcode 19,
assigning effEditIdle this opcode results in a correct rendering of
the plugin's window.

Therefor I strongly believe that effEditIdle = 19

gui: Fix window having leftovers from past updates

We should manually paint background.

closes #127
ci: Fix wrong name for macos archive

ci: Disable parallel build on Ubuntu to prevent oom

It seems release build ooms on gcc for whatever reason.
tests: Fix wrong comparison left after local tests
readme: Small update for PulseAudio

tests: Reduce time of "All options" test

Using REQUIRE from catch2 in a hot loop is terrible for performance.
readme: Small update

common: Do not wait for frames when receiving large input

For offline processing hosts could pass a lot of frames at once,
there is also no indicator whether additional frames are expected.
By default, we accumulate enough output frame to write sampleFrames
number of frames into output, however with large input we have to
output what we have and zero out the rest. Otherwise, we'd have too
much output buffered and never written.

Fixes compatibility with Audacity. 500 ms cut-off is arbitrary.

cmake: Enable lto for releases

lto considerably reduces library size, by around 50%. However,
there are still parts of JUCE compiled in that we don't need.

For this add BUILD_FOR_RELEASE option given which we enable lto,
later other optimizations or build steps could be added to it.

cmake: Support install target for Unix systems

JUCE has a terrible idea of installing plugin during the BUILD process
instead of during the INSTALL, also JUCE wants to install its headers
which we don't want at all. So it's easier to handle it ourselves.

cmake: Add BUILD_VERSION as cmake parameter

Allows to automatically pass version to juce configuration during
new version release.

JUCE: Disable LTO for juceaide to save build time

Use JUCE, new parameters, stereo, tests

This is a huge BREAKING refactoring. If you load LADSPA plugin with
pulseaudio - it will be BROKEN because new parameters are added.

JUCE has GPLv3 license so we could use it and change however we want.

JUCE brings us the following benefits:
- We could support all plugins which JUCE supports without any
  additional code for each plugin. Now supported via JUCE:
  - all systems: LV2 VST VST3
  - macOS only: AU AUv3
- Better compatibility with different plugin hosts.
- Easy to use FST headers instead of VST2. FST is an open-source
  reverse-engineered headers for VST2; they are needed because
  VST2 license does not permit its usage.
- GUI!

Downsides are:
- Longer compile times;
- Bigger library sizes;
- Have to vendor JUCE (via git subproject) in order to patch it.

- New parameter: retroactive VAD grace period - it introduces some
  latency and in return allows to fix a small cut off at sentence start.
- Reworked block processing to be more modular/readable and support
  blocks with variable frames count (e.g. used by Audacity).

Tests are implemented via catch2. Tests aren't checking much, but should
be enough to check undefined behavior and memory corruption.

Build artifacts for Windows, Linux, macOS on CI.
